    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-09-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-09-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="1013"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1013">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.6354/146: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kennedy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-09-14">September 14,
                            1939</date>.<lb/>[Received September 14—11:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1641. I have again talked to Malcolm MacDonald. At the close of the tin market
                    yesterday the buffer stock pool had apparently exhausted its resources and since
                    there was no supply of tin available it was deemed advisable to close the
                    market, particularly in view of the conference to be held tomorrow mentioned in
                    my 1625, September 13.<note n="89" xml:id="d1013fn89">Not printed; it stated
                        that “the Dutch are coming over on Friday to meet Campbell and the British
                        Metal Controller to work out a long range tin policy.” (811.24 Raw
                        Materials/318)</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kennedy</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
